Package org.pepstock.charba.client.geo

Class JsGeoHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.geo.JsGeoHelper
  • final class JsGeoHelper
extends Object
    Internal utility for GEo charts to invoke ChartGeo.topojson utility provided by the controller package.
    TopoJson is packaged with this plugin to convert data, it is exposed as in the global context.
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero

      • features

        ArrayObject features​(TopoJson topojson,
                     String featureProperty)
        Parses the topoJson definition in order to create all features need to draw the regions.
        Parameters:
        topojson - topoJson region definition
        featureProperty - property in the objects node of topoJson definition where all regions are defined
        Returns:
        array with all parsed features

      • projection

        ArrayDouble projection​(Chart chart,
                       double latitude,
                       double longitude)
        Translates latitude and longitude in coordinates of the canvas where the chart is drawn.
        Parameters:
        chart - native chart instance
        latitude - latitude to use to get the Y point
        longitude - longitude to use to get the X point
        Returns:
        an array of double with X (index 0) and Y (index 1) or null if chart is not consistent

      • invert

        ArrayDouble invert​(Chart chart,
                   double x,
                   double y)
        Translates X and Y coordinates of the canvas where the chart is drawn in latitude and longitude.
        Parameters:
        chart - native chart instance
        x - coordinate X of the canvas to translate in longitude
        y - coordinate Y of the canvas to translate in latitude
        Returns:
        an array of double with longitude (index 0) and latitude (index 1) or null if chart is not consistent
